1
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,000
You missed one.

2
00:00:13,067 --> 00:00:14,533
Promise, Mommy.

3
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:16,500
I will never leave you.

4
00:00:16,567 --> 00:00:17,767
Liar!

5
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:18,800
Hurry up.

6
00:00:18,867 --> 00:00:21,167
The woman's here.
She's getting out of the hotel.

7
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:22,900
We're about to leave...

8
00:00:22,967 --> 00:00:25,267
All right.
We're almost there, Bukoy.

9
00:00:25,333 --> 00:00:28,333
Here! Here are the keys.
I took it from your mom's room.

10
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,433
- Darn you!
- Ma'am! Ma'am!

11
00:00:32,067 --> 00:00:35,900
I need to put you
in a medically induced coma.

12
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,067
Emma! Emma!

13
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:39,733
Mookie found out
she wasn't sick.

14
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:42,500
Ma'am Olive made everything up.

15
00:00:42,567 --> 00:00:44,100
Don't spit it out! Drink it!

16
00:00:44,167 --> 00:00:45,267
Mookie!

17
00:00:47,133 --> 00:00:48,800
Darn it!

18
00:00:48,867 --> 00:00:50,433
What right do you have to come

19
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:52,133
and look
for someone else's child?

20
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,800
I know what you did to Mookie.

21
00:00:54,867 --> 00:00:55,967
Bring Mookie out.

22
00:01:30,367 --> 00:01:33,533
How dare you come
into my house at this hour...

23
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,967
and tell me to bring Mookie out?

24
00:01:37,933 --> 00:01:39,200
Why? Who are you?

25
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,633
Are you her mother?

26
00:01:41,733 --> 00:01:42,800
Mother?

27
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:46,867
No sensible mother
would give veterinary medicine

28
00:01:46,933 --> 00:01:48,300
to her own child!

29
00:01:48,367 --> 00:01:50,633
Is that what this woman
told you?

30
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:51,900
Isn't it true, Ma'am?

31
00:01:51,967 --> 00:01:53,633
Shut up!

32
00:01:53,700 --> 00:01:55,767
Didn't I fire you?

33
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:58,067
Do you believe that woman?

34
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:01,900
Wait.

35
00:02:03,167 --> 00:02:06,233
Why am I explaining to you?

36
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:08,267
- Get out of my house!
- I'm not going anywhere!

37
00:02:08,333 --> 00:02:10,500
- Get lost!
- Mookie needs me!

38
00:02:10,567 --> 00:02:14,067
- Get out of here! Get lost!
- Mookie needs me!

39
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:14,967
- Mookie!
- Let go of me!

40
00:02:17,533 --> 00:02:19,233
- Mookie!
- Let go of me!

41
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:21,167
Let go of me!

42
00:02:21,233 --> 00:02:25,800
Mommy Emma! Mommy Emma!

43
00:02:25,867 --> 00:02:27,733
- Mookie!
- Mom!

44
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,667
Mom! I'm right here, Mom!

45
00:02:29,733 --> 00:02:30,767
Mom!

46
00:02:31,933 --> 00:02:34,233
- Mookie! Mookie!
- Mom! Mom!

47
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:35,300
What happened to you?

48
00:02:35,367 --> 00:02:36,767
- Mom!
- What did she do to you?

49
00:02:36,833 --> 00:02:40,200
The keys are in the basket
of stuffed toys.

50
00:02:40,267 --> 00:02:41,633
- Keys?
- Yes.

51
00:02:42,567 --> 00:02:44,067
Where?

52
00:02:44,133 --> 00:02:47,700
I called Astrid
before facing you.

53
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,233
And she's bringing the police!

54
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:52,067
You and Emma
will end up in jail.

55
00:02:52,133 --> 00:02:55,133
And I'll make sure
you two will rot in there!

56
00:02:56,900 --> 00:02:58,767
- Where is it?
- On the other side!

57
00:02:58,833 --> 00:02:59,667
There you go, Mom.

58
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:03,133
Got it.

59
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:08,333
I don't know which key it is.

60
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,100
Wait.

61
00:03:10,067 --> 00:03:11,600
Mookie!

62
00:03:11,667 --> 00:03:12,767
Emma!

63
00:03:16,667 --> 00:03:17,600
We're getting out of here, okay?

64
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:19,000
We're getting out of here.

65
00:03:19,067 --> 00:03:21,633
- Emma!
- Where's the key?

66
00:03:21,733 --> 00:03:24,700
Mom. Mom, I also don't know.

67
00:03:24,767 --> 00:03:26,033
Mom! Mom! Mom!

68
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:27,267
- Mommy, please!
- I told you

69
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:30,400
to leave my daughter
and me alone!

70
00:03:30,467 --> 00:03:31,767
Mommy, please!

71
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:33,867
- Mommy!
- Why don't you want

72
00:03:33,933 --> 00:03:35,100
to leave us alone?

73
00:03:35,167 --> 00:03:37,000
Why don't you want
to leave my daughter alone?

74
00:03:37,067 --> 00:03:39,267
Mommy! Stop!

75
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:41,233
Stop hurting Mommy Emma!

76
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:42,633
- Get lost!
- How could you do this

77
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:44,833
- to your daughter?
- Mommy! Mommy Emma!

78
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:45,900
Mommy, please!

79
00:03:45,967 --> 00:03:47,300
- Mookie, I'll save you!
- Get out of here!

80
00:03:47,367 --> 00:03:49,333
Get lost!

81
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,333
Mommy!

82
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:51,733
Mommy Emma!

83
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,433
I'll come back for you, Mookie!

84
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:28,167
You're messing around
with everything!

85
00:04:35,367 --> 00:04:36,800
Mookie is such a good kid.

86
00:04:36,867 --> 00:04:38,233
She doesn't deserve
to be treated like this!

87
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,267
Just let her go!

88
00:04:40,333 --> 00:04:41,700
What for?

89
00:04:41,767 --> 00:04:43,567
So you can take her
away from me?

90
00:04:43,633 --> 00:04:46,967
I'm not crazy to give
my daughter to you!

91
00:04:47,033 --> 00:04:48,367
You're crazy!

92
00:04:48,433 --> 00:04:51,600
No parent will chain
her own child!

93
00:04:51,667 --> 00:04:52,833
I'm not Mookie's blood relative,

94
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:55,167
but it hurts me
every time I see her suffer.

95
00:04:55,233 --> 00:04:57,200
But you, you're her mother!

96
00:04:57,267 --> 00:04:59,000
Why are you torturing her?

97
00:05:11,633 --> 00:05:14,767
Whatever I do to my child
is none of your business!

98
00:05:14,833 --> 00:05:15,367
Get lost!

99
00:05:15,433 --> 00:05:16,900
Get out of my house!

100
00:05:16,967 --> 00:05:19,367
- Let go of me!
- Get lost!

101
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:21,233
Let go of me! Mookie!

102
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:23,433
You're messing with everything!

103
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:25,567
Leave my daughter and me alone!

104
00:05:25,633 --> 00:05:27,667
- Get lost!
- I won't let you

105
00:05:27,733 --> 00:05:29,000
hurt Mookie again!

106
00:05:29,067 --> 00:05:30,533
I will report you to the police!

107
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,567
Do so!

108
00:05:31,633 --> 00:05:33,933
Let's see who they will believe!

109
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,567
I said let go of me!

110
00:05:37,167 --> 00:05:38,267
Stop it!

111
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:39,367
Stop!

112
00:05:39,433 --> 00:05:41,367
- Ma'am Astrid!
- Help me get this trash out!

113
00:05:41,433 --> 00:05:42,700
- Hurry!
- Ma'am Astrid!

114
00:05:42,767 --> 00:05:46,400
Ma'am Astrid, I know you're not
evil like your friend.

115
00:05:46,467 --> 00:05:51,600
She can't stay here long!
She can't stay here long!

116
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:53,900
- Get lost!
- Ma'am Astrid, please help her!

117
00:05:53,967 --> 00:05:55,100
She needs help...

118
00:05:56,067 --> 00:05:57,167
Get lost!

119
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,167
Ma'am Astrid!

120
00:06:02,233 --> 00:06:04,967
Ma'am Astrid,
please help Mookie!

121
00:06:05,033 --> 00:06:06,667
Ma'am Astrid!

122
00:06:06,733 --> 00:06:07,967
Olive.

123
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:09,333
What's going on?

124
00:06:10,033 --> 00:06:11,433
- Ma'am Astrid.
- Save that for later.

125
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,767
Ma'am Astrid!

126
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:24,467
Just wait for me here.

127
00:06:25,433 --> 00:06:27,433
Why do you seem
to not want me to see Mookie?

128
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:32,233
It's not like that.

129
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:34,967
Don't tell me
Emma's telling the truth?

130
00:06:35,033 --> 00:06:37,867
That Mookie needs my help.

131
00:06:37,933 --> 00:06:42,867
I'm just making sure she can't
escape again to go to Emma.

132
00:06:42,967 --> 00:06:44,500
Did you give her canixidol?

133
00:06:46,033 --> 00:06:49,067
Only one vial remained
from the ones Mookie destroyed.

134
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:52,167
The medicine
will take effect tomorrow.

135
00:06:52,233 --> 00:06:55,600
Olive, can you please stop?

136
00:06:55,667 --> 00:06:59,600
Stop giving her medicines
she doesn't need.

137
00:06:59,667 --> 00:07:02,033
And please,
bring her back to her room!

138
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:06,933
We'll talk later.

139
00:07:24,867 --> 00:07:26,567
Mookie!

140
00:07:42,867 --> 00:07:44,067
Mookie.

141
00:07:50,367 --> 00:07:51,700
What are you looking at?

142
00:07:53,533 --> 00:07:54,500
Nothing.

143
00:08:08,367 --> 00:08:10,433
Ma'am Astrid!

144
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:12,300
Ma'am Astrid!

145
00:08:12,367 --> 00:08:14,600
Ma'am Astrid,
please help Mookie!

146
00:08:14,667 --> 00:08:15,800
Ma'am Astrid!

147
00:08:15,867 --> 00:08:17,500
- Ma'am Astrid!
- Emma!

148
00:08:19,033 --> 00:08:19,800
Emma!

149
00:08:20,733 --> 00:08:21,467
Come!

150
00:08:22,233 --> 00:08:23,567
Dan.

151
00:08:23,633 --> 00:08:24,267
Come here.

152
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:32,200
The barangay officials
didn't come with me.

153
00:08:32,267 --> 00:08:34,300
Dan. Dan, I saw Mookie.

154
00:08:34,367 --> 00:08:35,533
She's chained.

155
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,033
She needs our help.

156
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:38,767
She needs help.

157
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:40,433
But the barangay chairman
is right.

158
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,700
We don't have enough proof.

159
00:08:42,767 --> 00:08:46,800
We need to get solid proof
against Olive.

160
00:08:54,633 --> 00:08:57,300
Emma wouldn't hear you...

161
00:08:59,967 --> 00:09:01,400
if you...

162
00:09:04,067 --> 00:09:06,400
hadn't screamed.

163
00:09:08,433 --> 00:09:11,333
She already knows
your situation.

164
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,900
We need to leave.

165
00:09:16,467 --> 00:09:18,033
We need to get away.

166
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,567
I don't want to, Mommy.

167
00:09:19,633 --> 00:09:20,833
Why?

168
00:09:20,900 --> 00:09:22,767
Because you don't want
to be away from Emma?

169
00:09:22,833 --> 00:09:23,967
Is that it?

170
00:09:24,033 --> 00:09:25,967
What do we do?
Will we just leave Mookie be?

171
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:27,633
What if she gets harmed?

172
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:30,533
You didn't see her struggle.

173
00:09:30,633 --> 00:09:33,300
You don't know
how tough it is for me.

174
00:09:33,367 --> 00:09:36,800
Olive might send you to jail
if we attack her without proof.

175
00:09:36,867 --> 00:09:40,333
I'm just worried for you,
she might have you arrested.

176
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:44,733
Emma, you won't be able to help
Mookie if you're in jail.

177
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:45,833
Please listen to me.

178
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:47,667
Dan! Dan!

179
00:09:47,733 --> 00:09:50,800
I saw Mookie chained like a dog!

180
00:09:50,867 --> 00:09:52,967
I'll help you with Mookie,
but...

181
00:09:54,567 --> 00:09:56,433
let's go home for now.

182
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:59,300
Please listen to me.

183
00:10:02,867 --> 00:10:03,667
Let's go.

184
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,967
Do you remember this?

185
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:47,733
Here you go, Mookie.

186
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,133
This is what you want me
to get for you.

187
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:51,233
- Thank you, Flor.
- Okay.

188
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:00,900
Mommy.

189
00:11:04,467 --> 00:11:05,867
Flor, what's with you?

190
00:11:06,733 --> 00:11:08,400
Why did you bring Mookie here?

191
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:10,933
She might catch my illness.
Go on.

192
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,800
- Ma'am...
- Bring her inside.

193
00:11:12,867 --> 00:11:15,433
Mookie insisted, Ma'am.

194
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:17,267
Don't worry, Mommy.

195
00:11:17,333 --> 00:11:18,967
I'm taking vitamins.

196
00:11:19,033 --> 00:11:20,433
So I won't catch your illness.

197
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:22,467
No. Go inside.

198
00:11:22,533 --> 00:11:24,500
Go, I don't want you
to catch my illness.

199
00:11:25,533 --> 00:11:26,467
Okay.

200
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:37,933
Mommy, don't worry about me.

201
00:11:38,567 --> 00:11:39,967
I'm okay.

202
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:44,833
You always take care of me.

203
00:11:44,933 --> 00:11:48,567
So I want to be
your doctor this time.

204
00:11:49,867 --> 00:11:53,267
I'm glad you gave me
this stethoscope.

205
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:04,267
Oh no, Mommy!

206
00:12:05,467 --> 00:12:07,900
Your heart is racing.

207
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:11,200
It's because you overwork.

208
00:12:12,233 --> 00:12:16,133
So take your medicine
so you'll feel better.

209
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,500
You know what, Mookie?

210
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:24,033
I get stronger
whenever you're by my side.

211
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:30,533
You are the only medicine
for my illness.

212
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,433
Always remember, Mommy...

213
00:12:33,133 --> 00:12:35,333
I will never leave you.

214
00:12:36,567 --> 00:12:39,500
- You promise?
- Promise.

215
00:12:43,167 --> 00:12:48,600
You know, when I get better,
I'll go to medical school.

216
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:52,000
I'll be a doctor like you.

217
00:12:52,067 --> 00:12:57,000
And I will take care of you
until you grow old.

218
00:12:59,533 --> 00:13:00,767
Love you, Mommy.

219
00:13:04,333 --> 00:13:06,667
Do you remember this, Mookie?

220
00:13:09,467 --> 00:13:11,967
We were happy, right?

221
00:13:15,300 --> 00:13:16,967
When it was just the two of us.

222
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,467
When Emma wasn't messing
with our lives.

223
00:13:23,567 --> 00:13:26,233
Mommy Emma isn't messing
with us.

224
00:13:27,667 --> 00:13:31,000
She just doesn't want
to see me suffer.

225
00:13:31,067 --> 00:13:33,067
She doesn't want to see you
torturing me.

226
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:36,733
I don't want to be away
from her.

227
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:39,733
The truth has come out!

228
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:45,267
You don't want
to be away from Emma!

229
00:13:50,367 --> 00:13:51,533
Okay, Mookie.

230
00:13:54,867 --> 00:13:57,667
I'll be understanding for now.

231
00:13:57,733 --> 00:13:58,633
Mommy...

232
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:02,467
But once we get out of here...

233
00:14:03,933 --> 00:14:06,600
you'll again get used...

234
00:14:06,667 --> 00:14:09,300
- to just being the two of us.
- Mommy, please stop.

235
00:14:16,767 --> 00:14:19,333
Emma can't mess with us anymore.

236
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:23,967
Mommy, please.
I don't want to leave, Mommy!

237
00:14:24,433 --> 00:14:26,633
Mommy!

238
00:14:31,267 --> 00:14:31,800
What?

239
00:14:33,233 --> 00:14:36,633
Olive chains Mookie
like an animal?

240
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:38,700
Oh, God...

241
00:14:38,767 --> 00:14:41,567
that woman is a beast.

242
00:14:41,633 --> 00:14:44,133
I don't think I can sit still.

243
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:47,500
I'll testify that her mom
is abusing her

244
00:14:47,567 --> 00:14:49,567
if the barangay officials
don't believe it.

245
00:14:50,867 --> 00:14:54,200
The barangay cops must get
inside Olive's house.

246
00:14:54,267 --> 00:14:57,867
So they'll see
what she's doing to Mookie!

247
00:14:57,933 --> 00:15:00,467
But, Mother,
I don't think we can convince

248
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:03,100
the barangay
to enter Olive's house.

249
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:06,067
Because we don't have
solid proof against them.

250
00:15:07,533 --> 00:15:09,367
But we must get Mookie.

251
00:15:09,433 --> 00:15:11,900
Or the DSWD can get her.

252
00:15:11,967 --> 00:15:14,900
What matters is to save her
from her mom's abuse.

253
00:15:14,967 --> 00:15:18,467
The barangay officials told me
it'll be sufficient evidence

254
00:15:18,533 --> 00:15:21,700
if we catch Olive
in the act of hurting Mookie.

255
00:15:21,767 --> 00:15:22,900
A video.

256
00:15:24,033 --> 00:15:26,000
But we don't have that.

257
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:27,900
What do we do?

258
00:15:27,967 --> 00:15:29,800
Are we just going
to abandon Mookie?

259
00:15:30,933 --> 00:15:33,533
We couldn't catch
Kayla's kidnapper.

260
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,600
Are we not going
to help Mookie, too?

261
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:40,933
What if she's like Mookie
who's struggling right now?

262
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:45,467
I'd rather have someone
who cares and helps her.

263
00:15:45,533 --> 00:15:48,000
So, I know
she has someone to lean on.

264
00:15:50,133 --> 00:15:53,400
There's nothing I can do
for my child.

265
00:15:53,467 --> 00:15:55,900
But if we can help Mookie,

266
00:15:55,967 --> 00:15:58,733
it'll feel like we've already
helped our daughter, Dan.

267
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:17,600
Don't worry too much, Astrid.

268
00:16:18,633 --> 00:16:21,367
I'm not doing anything bad
to Mookie.

269
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:24,833
I will only believe you
once I see her.

270
00:16:26,033 --> 00:16:29,567
Are we going to fight
about this?

271
00:16:29,633 --> 00:16:32,233
Or are you waiting for me
to get mad at you again?

272
00:16:33,133 --> 00:16:35,200
I'm only concerned for the kid.

273
00:16:35,267 --> 00:16:36,933
I don't want her to get harmed.

274
00:17:00,067 --> 00:17:01,600
Please, please.

275
00:17:02,933 --> 00:17:07,633
Mookie can stay with me if you
want to keep her away from Emma.

276
00:17:07,700 --> 00:17:09,933
I will take care of her.

277
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:10,767
You?

278
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:15,800
What do you know about
caring for a kid?

279
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:17,567
You don't have a family.

280
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:19,700
But, Olive...

281
00:17:19,767 --> 00:17:21,800
Let's end this conversation.

282
00:17:23,233 --> 00:17:24,767
And I'm warning you, Astrid.

283
00:17:25,933 --> 00:17:28,633
Don't ever try
to betray me again.

284
00:17:29,667 --> 00:17:33,900
If you want to keep
the good life that I give you.

285
00:17:41,967 --> 00:17:43,133
Please!

286
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:58,967
I can do this. I can do this.

287
00:17:59,033 --> 00:18:01,867
Mommy Emma said
I need to bear it.

288
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:47,200
- Mookie! What happened to you?
- Mom!

289
00:18:47,267 --> 00:18:49,233
The keys
are in the stuffed toys.

290
00:18:49,300 --> 00:18:51,600
Mom! Mommy, please!

291
00:18:51,667 --> 00:18:53,733
Won't you really leave us alone?

292
00:19:08,100 --> 00:19:08,767
Flor?

293
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:20,633
Hello, Ando.

294
00:19:21,867 --> 00:19:24,333
Is the other rest house ready?

295
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:26,367
I won't come back
to the ancestral house.

296
00:19:26,433 --> 00:19:28,700
Someone else already
knows that place.

297
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:30,367
Yes, Ma'am.

298
00:19:30,433 --> 00:19:32,200
I've prepared the rest house.

299
00:19:33,067 --> 00:19:34,267
Good.

300
00:19:35,100 --> 00:19:40,067
I don't want anyone to know
about the new rest house.

301
00:19:40,133 --> 00:19:40,967
Yes, Ma'am.

302
00:20:22,433 --> 00:20:23,367
Emma?

303
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,067
Emma?

304
00:20:27,133 --> 00:20:27,833
Mom.

305
00:20:28,633 --> 00:20:29,233
Mom.

306
00:20:30,833 --> 00:20:32,233
Mom, where's Emma?

307
00:20:32,300 --> 00:20:33,867
Why are you looking for Emma?

308
00:20:33,933 --> 00:20:36,633
I saw you went
into the room together.

309
00:20:37,267 --> 00:20:39,400
I think she left.

310
00:20:39,467 --> 00:20:41,133
I don't know either.

311
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:43,633
I fell asleep here.
I didn't notice.

312
00:20:44,667 --> 00:20:46,533
Emma's unbelievable.

313
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:48,800
Where would she go at this hour?

314
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:55,467
Dan!
I saw Mookie chained like a dog!

315
00:20:55,533 --> 00:20:57,733
Even if she didn't say it,
she was asking for help.

316
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:58,833
I couldn't do anything!

317
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:01,467
Let's help her! Come on!

318
00:21:43,533 --> 00:21:44,833
Hurry, faster, faster.

319
00:21:48,067 --> 00:21:48,967
Flor.

320
00:21:49,033 --> 00:21:50,533
Thank you.

321
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:53,200
I really want to help Mookie.

322
00:21:53,267 --> 00:21:54,900
I know what we will do
is dangerous,

323
00:21:54,967 --> 00:21:59,133
but I really feel sorry
for Mookie.

324
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,533
Mommy!

325
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:07,433
Hello, Ando.

326
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:09,200
I can't hear you.

327
00:22:09,267 --> 00:22:11,967
There's no signal here.

328
00:22:12,033 --> 00:22:13,000
Oh, yes.

329
00:22:13,067 --> 00:22:14,100
Here.

330
00:22:14,167 --> 00:22:16,133
I brought the keys
to Ma'am Olive's house.

331
00:22:16,233 --> 00:22:17,500
We can get in.

332
00:22:17,567 --> 00:22:18,733
- Really?
- Yes.

333
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:20,500
Thank you.

334
00:22:20,567 --> 00:22:22,533
- Thank you. Let's go!
- Come on, let's hurry.

335
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:24,800
Oh! Before I forget,

336
00:22:24,867 --> 00:22:28,367
I also got Mookie's diary before
Ma'am Olive kicked me out.

337
00:22:28,433 --> 00:22:29,900
- Really?
- Yes.

338
00:22:29,967 --> 00:22:32,100
Mookie asked me a favor.

339
00:22:32,167 --> 00:22:35,667
Flor, please talk to Mommy Emma.

340
00:22:35,733 --> 00:22:37,800
I'm sure she can help us.

341
00:22:37,867 --> 00:22:40,100
- Okay.
- Flor, wait!

342
00:22:40,167 --> 00:22:42,100
My diary.

343
00:22:42,167 --> 00:22:43,767
Give it to her.

344
00:22:43,833 --> 00:22:47,133
Everything Mommy's doing to me
is written there.

345
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:50,467
Maybe we can use that diary
as proof against Ma'am Olive.

346
00:22:50,567 --> 00:22:51,767
You're right.

347
00:22:51,833 --> 00:22:56,333
But I'm sorry, I forgot to bring
it because I was in a hurry.

348
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:57,433
It's okay.

349
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:59,500
We have to save Mookie first.

350
00:22:59,567 --> 00:23:01,600
- Okay? Let's go.
- Okay. Let's go.

351
00:23:44,167 --> 00:23:46,200
Mookie!

352
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:52,600
I thought you gave her
canixidol?

353
00:23:52,667 --> 00:23:54,067
How did she manage to escape?

354
00:23:54,133 --> 00:23:55,433
The medicine hasn't
taken effect yet.

355
00:23:55,533 --> 00:23:56,700
That's why she can still move.

356
00:23:56,767 --> 00:24:00,667
No matter what Olive does
to that kid, she's her child.

357
00:24:00,733 --> 00:24:03,167
And because you took her child,

358
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:04,700
she can file a complaint
against you.

359
00:24:04,767 --> 00:24:07,067
You'll end up in jail.

360
00:24:07,133 --> 00:24:08,233
Give her back.

361
00:24:08,300 --> 00:24:10,567
I will get Mookie
back from Emma.

362
00:24:10,633 --> 00:24:13,433
Wherever they hide,
I will find them.

363
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:17,833
And I will not stop
until I get my daughter back!

364
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:22,033
This is a big problem.
And we really can't hide her.

365
00:24:22,100 --> 00:24:23,667
It's kidnapping.

366
00:24:23,733 --> 00:24:27,800
I can think of someone Mookie
could run to for help.

367
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:32,267
And that someone might know
where Mookie is.

368
00:24:33,333 --> 00:24:34,300
Who?

369
00:24:34,367 --> 00:24:36,633
Emma, let's meet.

370
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:39,100
I'll give you Mookie's diary.
